  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Hardware retail manager",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Role Overview</strong></h3><p>We are looking for a hands-on <strong>Retail Manager</strong> to lead the launch and daily operations of our brand-new hardware storefront. You will be responsible for everything from the initial shop setup to building a high-performing sales team. If you are a hardware expert who loves being on the shop floor and building processes from scratch, this is the role for you.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p><strong>Store Launch:</strong> Manage the initial setup, including floor layout, shelving, POS system implementation, and stock procurement.</p></li><li><p><strong>Daily Operations:</strong> Spend the majority of your time on the floor leading sales, assisting customers with technical inquiries, and overseeing staff.</p></li><li><p><strong>Inventory Management:</strong> Take full ownership of stock-taking, merchandising, and monitoring inventory aging to minimize wastage.</p></li><li><p><strong>Team Leadership:</strong> Recruit, train, and roster a retail team, ensuring they meet our high standards for customer service and product knowledge.</p></li><li><p><strong>Business Growth:</strong> Suggest and execute local marketing ideas to increase foot traffic and brand awareness in the community.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p><strong>Experience:</strong> Minimum 5 years in <strong>Hardware Retail Management</strong>.</p></li><li><p><strong>Proven Track Record:</strong> Experience in opening a new retail outlet from scratch is highly preferred.</p></li><li><p><strong>Technical Knowledge:</strong> Deep understanding of hardware products and the Singapore retail market.</p></li><li><p><strong>Work Style:</strong> A \"lead-by-example\" attitude; comfortable working on the shop floor and handling physical stock.</p></li><li><p><strong>Flexibility:</strong> Ability to work retail hours, including weekends and Public Holidays.</p></li></ul>",
